SIMPLE: gyroidal
RECORDS: 1

==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Gyroidal
<hw>Gy*roid"al</hw> <pr>(j⟦isl⟧*roid"⟦ait⟧l)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos>
<ety>[Gr. <grk>gy^ros</grk> circle + <ets>-oid</ets> +
<ets>-al</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>Spiral in arrangement or
action.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Crystallog.)</fld> <def>Having the planes arranged
spirally, so that they incline all to the right (or left) of a vertical
line; -- said of certain hemihedral forms.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>3.</sn> <fld>(Opt.)</fld> <def>Turning the plane of polarization
circularly or spirally to the right or left.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Gyrolepis</ent>⟦br⟧
\'d8
